From: wasm-nommu
Subject: libbb: compile out xfork()/xvfork_parent_waits_and_exits() on wasm when BB_MMU=1

The existing #if BB_MMU guard on xfork() was designed for uClibc NOMMU
systems.  wasm32 busybox builds that use allnoconfig (e.g. ash.nix) do
NOT set CONFIG_NOMMU=y (ash depends on !NOMMU in Kconfig), so BB_MMU=1
and xfork() is compiled — but wasm musl ships no fork() symbol (fork is
unimplementable on the clone-with-fn NOMMU model).

xvfork_parent_waits_and_exits() was already given a !BB_MMU abort-stub
by patch 0004 (NOMMU busybox builds), but the BB_MMU=1 code path still
calls xvfork() → vfork(), which is also absent on wasm musl.

This patch (applies after 0004) adds __wasm__ guards for both functions
so the ash.nix allnoconfig build links cleanly.

Applied after patch 0004 (which added #if !BB_MMU/#else/#endif to
xvfork_parent_waits_and_exits); this patch extends the #else chain with
#elif defined(__wasm__) so the wasm+BB_MMU=1 path also aborts loudly
without referencing the absent vfork symbol.

--- a/libbb/xfuncs_printf.c
+++ b/libbb/xfuncs_printf.c
@@ -669,7 +669,8 @@
 	buf[4 + 2 + 2] = (buf[4 + 2 + 2] & 0x3f) | 0x80;
 }

-#if BB_MMU
+/* wasm32: no fork even with BB_MMU=1 (allnoconfig ash build). */
+#if BB_MMU && !defined(__wasm__)
 pid_t FAST_FUNC xfork(void)
 {
 	pid_t pid;
@@ -687,6 +688,10 @@
 	 * equivalent). Its only callers (nsenter/unshare) are disabled here, so
 	 * it is unreachable — abort loudly rather than reference the absent vfork. */
 	bb_simple_error_msg_and_die("xvfork_parent_waits_and_exits: unsupported on NOMMU");
+#elif defined(__wasm__)
+	/* wasm32 with BB_MMU=1: fork/vfork absent (wasm NOMMU model).
+	 * Callers (nsenter/unshare) disabled; abort loudly. */
+	bb_simple_error_msg_and_die("xvfork_parent_waits_and_exits: unsupported on wasm");
 #else
 	pid_t pid;
